description: Write a Python function to find the GCD of two positive integers.
input_format: Two space-separated integers a and b (1 <= a, b <= 10^9).
output_format: A single integer: the GCD of a and b.
prompt:
; Write a Python function to find the GCD of two positive integers.
; Input format: Two space-separated integers a and b (1 <= a, b <= 10^9).
; Output format: A single integer: the GCD of a and b.

#lang racket
completions:
(define (gcd a b)
  (if (= b 0)
      a
      (gcd b (modulo a b))))

; Example usage:
; (gcd 48 18) => 6
; (gcd 56 98) => 14

(define (gcd a b)
  (if (zero? b)
      a
      (gcd b (modulo a b))))

; Sample Input-Output Pairs
; (gcd 48 18) => 6
; (gcd 100 25) => 25
; (gcd 7 3) => 1

(define (gcd a b)
  (if (zero? b)
      a
      (gcd b (remainder a b))))

; Sample Input-Output Pairs
; (gcd 48 18) => 6
; (gcd 100 25) => 25
; (gcd 7 5) => 1

(define (gcd a b)

      a
      (gcd b (remainder a b))))
